    b.
        i.
            A person with anaemia is often tired because they don't have enough red blood cells. Red blood cells deliver oxygen to cells for aerobic respiration, which produces energy. Without enough red blood cells, the person's cells will not have enough oxygen so will not have enough energy as they cannot respire aerobically, and anaerobic respiration produces less energy, so the person has less energy, which means they are often tired.
        ii.
            A person with leukopena is more likely to get infections because they don't have enough white blood cells. White blood cells prevent infections by producing antibodies and engulfing pathogens, so not enough white blood cells would mean that they are more likely to get infections as it would take longer to fight off bacteria.
