    d.
        There is indeed a lower percentage of people having heart attacks in the statin group. This may indicate that statins reduce the risk of heart attacks.

        However, only one type of statin was tested. It may be that only that type of statin reduces the risk of heart attacks.

        In addition, we do not know how many people are in each group of people. It may be that there are not enough people to make sure that that difference in percentage of heart attacks is not just random noise.

        Moreover, the scientist only tracks the people for four years. If statins increase the risk of heart attacks massively after four years, this experiment will not discover that, and the conclusion will be false.
