        ii?
            The mean number of sperm released is a better measure of fertility than semen volume or sperm concentration because semen volume has little bearing on fertility -- it is the sperm that fertilises; so long as there is enough semen to deliver the sperm it has no other bearing. Mean sperm released is better than mean sperm concentration because this means there is more sperm which means it is more likely some will survive and reach the egg; increase in concentration (but decrease in actual number released) will not do this.
